David Duchovny, 62, clasped hands with his girlfriend Monique Pendleberry, 29, last night at the premiere of his new Netflix film, You People. The Hollywood actor wore a black velvet coat over a blue shirt featuring a white trim, paired with grey jeans. David held hands with his girlfriend as they walked the LA red carpet side by side. Monique also wore a black coat over a lacy top and blue trousers, paired with black heels. The loved-up couple have been together since 2017 after reportedly meeting at SunLie Organics Juicery, which David's friend owns and where Monique was an employee.